result.name: 阿一豬扒酸辣米綫

reviews.text: Regular, pork chop rice noodles in xichuan hot, spicy and sour soup. Expansive, 50 Hong Kong dollars. Marinated cucumbers is too sour.

It was OK. Signature pork noodle soup was OK. Didn't finish it. We also got the pork trotter and jellyfish dry noodle and it was not very good. Pork was very salty and small portioned. At first I thought they hadn't brought it out yet, like it was going to be on another plate, but then found it under the other stuff. Ehh... stick with the signature dish. Drinks were also just OK.
Their pork and shrimp ball noodles are nice. Although it is a bit expensive compared to other local restaurants, their foods are worth for every penny you spend.
After a disappointing lunch at a place nearby we decided to put up with some extra calories of a second lunch for this familiar, time-proven treat. Fantastic value for money. Mission accomplished.
a nice place to experience local noodle at mid price in Sai Ying Pun lol

reviews.text: Good fried pork chop and noodles for an okay price. I got the mildly spicy option and it was pretty spicy compared to other mildly spicy options I've had in Hong Kong in my opinion. Okay portion size. English menu and staff understands English. Limited seating. Fast service.

Great...
I did not a chance to take photo as I ran out of batterry  :'(
Noodles are well-cooked—bouncy, good texture. The spicy soup is indeed spicy but kind of one-dimensional. Pork chop that comes with the noodle soup is great—super tender and tasty.

food is excellent. my favourite is the pork chop noodle, and definitely with the spicy soup base! however, hygiene is pretty bad (typical old style kitchen), so not recommend to people who take food or store hygiene as priority!
fast and cheap place for lunch!
The earliest "四川" spicy flavor found in Hong Kong island,  2 branch.
